Very tasty! I wanted to flesh this out into a more complete meal, so I added 1/4 cup fresh coriander, 1/2 cup fresh bean sprouts, and a sweet red pepper, sliced. I also used mixed baby greens instead of the romaine and doubled the dressing ingredients. That way, I had extra dressing to marinate the steak in for an hour before cooking. This would be great for a casual dinner party on a hot summer day.

